WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:12.222 --> 01:15.214
[MAN LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

02:11.881 --> 02:13.212
SHELBY:
God.

02:13.383 --> 02:15.351
How long have I been out?

02:15.518 --> 02:16.951
About an hour.

02:17.120 --> 02:18.348
Where are we?

02:18.521 --> 02:20.250
ROB:
We just crossed the state line.

02:20.423 --> 02:21.754
- Really?
- Mm-hm.

02:21.925 --> 02:23.620
Already?

02:25.528 --> 02:27.007
Mm.
Why do I smell food?

02:30.500 --> 02:32.593
ROB: There should be a girlie toy
in there for you.

02:32.769 --> 02:35.533
SHELBY: Thanks, sweetie.
- Yeah.

02:42.312 --> 02:45.679
Jesus, Rob, slow down.
You're driving over a hundred.

02:45.849 --> 02:48.283
- I've got a really good convoy going here.
- No.

02:48.451 --> 02:50.817
Just slow down. Now.

03:02.866 --> 03:04.697
Thank you.

03:06.769 --> 03:08.236
Look...

03:08.538 --> 03:10.403
...okay, I know we had a shitty weekend.

03:10.573 --> 03:15.567
I wanna get home too.
But let's just do it safely, okay?

03:16.279 --> 03:18.270
No more bad luck.

03:18.448 --> 03:19.938
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

03:40.536 --> 03:43.562
Oh, I got the spot.

03:44.073 --> 03:45.370
"I love you too, Shelby."

03:45.708 --> 03:47.073
I love you too.

03:47.243 --> 03:48.801
I do.

03:48.978 --> 03:51.446
I'm wide awake so get some sleep.

03:51.614 --> 03:54.481
- Okay. Thank you, sweetie.
ROB: Mm-hm.

03:59.756 --> 04:02.554
[TRUCK HORN BLARING]

04:09.966 --> 04:11.433
Ah. Bingo.

04:30.353 --> 04:32.913
- Hey, you knocked out another hour.
- Ugh.

04:33.189 --> 04:35.817
I only feel more tired.

04:38.361 --> 04:39.692
Are you tired yet?

04:40.229 --> 04:41.662
Nope.

04:48.838 --> 04:51.432
I cannot believe you started another one.

04:51.607 --> 04:52.631
I didn't.

04:52.809 --> 04:54.538
- This one found me.
- Oh, whatever.

04:54.711 --> 04:58.203
Look at the speedometer.
It's like 12 miles over the speed limit.

04:58.381 --> 05:01.782
The other one, you were right.
It was too fast and unsafe.

05:01.951 --> 05:04.112
- This one isn't.
- Oh, please.

05:04.287 --> 05:07.484
Seriously, there's like an art
to a good convoy, babe.

05:07.657 --> 05:11.991
It's like a conversation between us
and the cars as we drive. We communicate.

05:12.161 --> 05:16.120
No, did you see that? That's him warning
me that there's some slow cars up ahead...

05:16.299 --> 05:18.290
...so we're gonna have to pass them.

05:18.868 --> 05:21.735
Oh, that's pretty considerate.

05:22.105 --> 05:24.665
Oh, see, now this is what I like to call
a brake pumper.

05:24.841 --> 05:28.106
You think speeding's dangerous,
try driving behind this guy.

05:34.817 --> 05:36.341
Okay.

05:36.619 --> 05:39.782
At this speed, I'm fine with it.
Just don't go faster.

05:44.327 --> 05:46.158
ROB:
Oh, right on.

05:46.329 --> 05:49.059
I was wondering
when they were gonna need to fuel up next.

05:49.232 --> 05:50.597
Well, what do we do?

05:50.767 --> 05:53.065
Are we supposed to introduce ourselves,
say hi?

05:53.236 --> 05:54.260
I don't know.

05:54.437 --> 05:57.964
I mean, I've never actually met anyone
I've been in a convoy with.

06:01.244 --> 06:04.236
[TRUCK ENGINE DOWNSHIFTING]

06:23.299 --> 06:24.323
[TRUCK BRAKES HISS]

06:45.021 --> 06:47.182
BERT: Sure am glad we all had to stop.
Hey, I'm Bert.

06:47.356 --> 06:48.516
- Rob.
- Rob.

06:48.691 --> 06:49.851
- Hi.
- Oh, nice.

06:50.026 --> 06:52.426
You a Robert?

06:53.930 --> 06:56.125
Or a Roberto? Ha, ha.

06:56.966 --> 06:58.900
No, I'm just kidding. Ha.

06:59.135 --> 07:00.159
[SIGHS]

07:00.336 --> 07:03.999
- Hello. So where you headed there, Rob?
ROB: Uh, Cincinnati.

07:04.173 --> 07:05.197
BERT:
Oh, you're kidding.

07:05.374 --> 07:07.569
It'll be nice
to have some steady company.

07:07.743 --> 07:09.210
- Yeah, you bet. Yeah.
BERT: Yeah.

07:09.378 --> 07:10.640
[CHUCKLES]

07:11.681 --> 07:13.376
Okay. Uh, well...

07:14.283 --> 07:15.614
...see you inside.

07:15.785 --> 07:17.446
- Sure. Yeah.
- Kids want their chocolates.

07:17.854 --> 07:19.287
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

07:19.522 --> 07:21.149
All right.

07:24.527 --> 07:25.755
[CHUCKLES]

07:34.470 --> 07:35.562
[CASH REGISTER DINGS]

08:25.955 --> 08:27.980
Uh-oh. Looks like someone
got the munchies.

08:28.157 --> 08:29.181
Ha, ha, ha. Yeah.

08:29.358 --> 08:32.986
No, I'm just messing with you. Anyway,
uh, I was talking to this trucker inside.

08:33.162 --> 08:34.958
Not very chatty guy.

08:35.131 --> 08:38.032
Anyway, he said he got on
his, uh, radio-thingy.

08:38.201 --> 08:40.294
Said the interstate up ahead's
pretty wall-to-wall.

08:40.602 --> 08:41.626
ROB: Mm. Really?
- Hey?

08:41.804 --> 08:45.205
Trucker on my CB says
it ain't moving worth a damn out there.

08:45.374 --> 08:47.365
Told me a way around it, though, so...

08:47.543 --> 08:49.977
...you're more than welcome
to swing on in behind me.

08:50.146 --> 08:51.875
Come on. I could use the company.

08:52.281 --> 08:54.647
Road's a lonely place
when you're traveling solo.

08:55.051 --> 08:57.178
Yeah, you got it, man. Hey, thanks.

08:58.387 --> 08:59.513
No problem.

09:05.461 --> 09:07.452
[SIGN BUZZING]

09:07.964 --> 09:09.955
[TRUCK BEEPING]

09:21.377 --> 09:22.435
What'd you talk about?

09:22.612 --> 09:25.479
Oh, the interstate's jammed up ahead
so we're gonna go around.

09:25.648 --> 09:29.106
- Yeah, and Mr. Lonesome up front there...
SHELBY: Uh, he's not alone.

09:29.418 --> 09:31.818
Yeah, he is. That's what he said.

09:31.988 --> 09:34.548
Rob, he's not alone.
There's a girl with him. I saw her.

09:35.491 --> 09:37.425
Misunderstanding then.

09:37.593 --> 09:39.356
It's no big deal.

09:42.598 --> 09:44.156
You sure we should be doing this?

09:44.834 --> 09:47.462
Would you rather turn around
and crawl up the interstate?

09:47.637 --> 09:49.571
It's like a parking lot.

09:49.739 --> 09:50.763
SHELBY:
No.

09:50.940 --> 09:52.771
Guess we're fine.

10:04.654 --> 10:06.349
Great.

10:06.522 --> 10:07.887
It's the sticks, Shelby.

10:08.057 --> 10:09.888
People hunt out in the sticks.

10:41.290 --> 10:43.053
There, see? Did you see that?

10:45.494 --> 10:47.155
- What?
- In the window. Get closer.

10:47.330 --> 10:49.355
There is someone in there.

10:54.904 --> 10:57.805
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

10:59.108 --> 11:01.076
[GRUNTS]

11:09.819 --> 11:11.081
SHELBY:
Hello? Hello?

11:11.454 --> 11:13.979
- Can you hear me?
- What the hell?

11:15.191 --> 11:17.318
You get his plates.
You get his license plates.

11:17.493 --> 11:21.156
- Shelby, come on.
- No, just go! Get his plates now! Go!

11:21.330 --> 11:22.991
- Just hurry up!
- Okay.

11:23.966 --> 11:25.490
SHELBY:
Okay.

11:27.636 --> 11:30.002
BERT: Is she okay? Is she alive?
SHELBY: Yeah.

11:34.243 --> 11:36.234
[TIRES SCREECHING]

11:56.332 --> 11:57.663
[LOOSE GRAVEL RUSTLING]

11:58.501 --> 12:00.492
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

12:58.694 --> 13:00.184
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

13:00.463 --> 13:01.487
[WOMAN COUGHING]

13:01.664 --> 13:02.790
- Get her up.
- There she is. There she is.

13:02.965 --> 13:04.125
Okay, she's back with us.

13:04.300 --> 13:07.736
SHELBY: Lift her up.
- You keep her coherent. I'll be right back.

13:08.838 --> 13:11.272
WOMAN: Keep him away from me.
- Oh, I will. It's okay.

13:11.440 --> 13:14.238
He threw you from the truck,
but he took off. You'll be fine.

13:14.410 --> 13:15.672
No, I jumped.

13:15.845 --> 13:17.403
What?

13:41.337 --> 13:43.237
[CRASHING]

13:45.107 --> 13:47.098
[CAR ENGINE HISSING]

13:48.811 --> 13:50.802
[GRUNTING]

13:55.518 --> 13:57.315
Shelby!

13:59.054 --> 14:00.851
Shelby!

14:06.095 --> 14:07.892
Are you okay?

14:09.231 --> 14:11.062
What happened?

14:11.233 --> 14:12.996
He... He...

14:13.168 --> 14:14.192
He came back.

14:14.370 --> 14:16.895
I know. I know.

14:17.172 --> 14:18.366
Where's my girlfriend?

14:18.541 --> 14:20.168
He took them.

14:20.342 --> 14:22.139
He took both of them.

14:22.311 --> 14:24.973
Both that lady and your girl.

14:25.447 --> 14:26.937
What?

14:27.816 --> 14:29.477
BERT:
He took off over there.

14:29.852 --> 14:31.479
Lift me up.

14:31.654 --> 14:34.282
- Help me up.
ROB: Yeah. Okay. Okay, come on.

14:39.628 --> 14:40.652
[PARKING BRAKE ENGAGES]

14:45.801 --> 14:49.362
BERT:
Wait, wait. Yeah, okay, all right.

14:49.605 --> 14:51.732
- You let me go.
- You're hurt. I'll go.

14:51.907 --> 14:56.003
Shhh. Just please promise me...

14:56.178 --> 14:58.908
...you take care of my family
if something happens, okay?

15:00.716 --> 15:03.708
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:08.390 --> 15:10.381
[CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

15:26.041 --> 15:28.373
TRYTON:
I don't know where I am.

15:28.544 --> 15:31.513
No, no, I was taking her to rehab.

15:31.981 --> 15:34.108
Don't know. Accident.

15:34.283 --> 15:36.342
Maybe she jumped.

15:36.652 --> 15:39.450
I don't know
because the bitch was crazy.

15:42.124 --> 15:43.614
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

15:47.630 --> 15:49.621
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

16:21.563 --> 16:23.554
[WOMAN WHIMPERING]

16:27.636 --> 16:29.069
[WOMAN WHIMPERING]

16:39.081 --> 16:40.275
[GRUNTING]

16:41.483 --> 16:42.711
[WHIMPERS]

16:45.387 --> 16:46.411
BERT:
Sorry.

16:46.989 --> 16:48.149
[CHUCKLES MANIACALLY]

16:48.323 --> 16:50.951
[MUFFLED]
Rob. Rob!

16:51.126 --> 16:52.150
Hold on, Shelby.

16:52.828 --> 16:54.261
[BERT LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

16:55.798 --> 16:57.129
[SHELBY SCREAMING]

17:00.302 --> 17:02.293
[SHELBY BREATHING HEAVILY]

17:02.471 --> 17:04.803
[DOOR HANDLE CLACKING]

17:07.309 --> 17:08.640
[SCREAMING INDISTINCTLY]

17:14.183 --> 17:15.207
[LAUGHS MANICALLY]

17:17.752 --> 17:20.654
You picked the wrong convoy, buddy.

17:22.290 --> 17:23.622
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

17:52.654 --> 17:54.019
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

17:58.160 --> 17:59.388
TABITHA:
Hello?

18:00.696 --> 18:02.687
Hello?

18:04.266 --> 18:06.257
[INDISTINCT TV CHATTER]

18:08.137 --> 18:10.970
- Hi, Tabby.
- Hey.

18:11.440 --> 18:13.772
Sorry I'm late.

18:13.942 --> 18:15.273
DANNY:
Huh.

18:16.979 --> 18:19.914
TABITHA: Hello?
- <i>Smoking.</i>

18:25.921 --> 18:27.354
[TABITHA GRUNTING]

18:27.623 --> 18:29.454
- Hey, Maxie.
- Hi.

18:33.529 --> 18:35.360
Danny, where's the babysitter?

18:35.531 --> 18:38.022
- She left already.
- Yeah, she lefted.

18:38.567 --> 18:39.591
What?

18:39.768 --> 18:41.531
Are you sure?

18:41.703 --> 18:43.000
[BANGING]

18:46.208 --> 18:47.368
TABITHA:
Hello?

18:48.143 --> 18:50.043
I'm here.

18:58.754 --> 19:00.745
[BOTH GIGGLING]

19:01.123 --> 19:04.092
[SOFA CUSHIONS SQUEAKING]

19:05.127 --> 19:07.721
Hello, it's Tabitha, the Carmines' niece.

19:08.297 --> 19:09.662
[MANIACAL CHUCKLING]

19:09.998 --> 19:11.158
[SIGHS]

19:11.333 --> 19:13.324
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

19:17.206 --> 19:18.230
[HANDS SLAP LEGS]

19:18.407 --> 19:20.705
[SIGHS]

19:26.682 --> 19:28.013
[DOOR CREAKS SHUT]

19:30.219 --> 19:33.188
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

19:53.275 --> 19:54.606
Okay.

19:55.410 --> 19:56.434
[SIGHS]

19:56.612 --> 19:58.603
What's next?

20:01.483 --> 20:03.280
"Quiet time."

20:06.355 --> 20:07.686
[BANGING UPSTAIRS]

20:10.959 --> 20:14.258
Boys, you're supposed to be quiet.

20:18.667 --> 20:19.998
[DOORBELL RINGS]

20:31.380 --> 20:33.041
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

20:46.828 --> 20:48.261
[THUNDER CRASHING]

20:50.666 --> 20:51.690
Hello?

20:52.567 --> 20:54.967
MAN:
Yes, hi. I'm here for June.

20:55.137 --> 20:57.605
June? There's no June here.

20:58.040 --> 21:01.203
MAN: Oh, well, no, she's been sitting
over here today.

21:01.376 --> 21:03.071
I dropped her off earlier.

21:03.245 --> 21:05.713
She missed cheerleading practice,
I'm getting worried.

21:05.881 --> 21:07.212
I'm her boyfriend, Owen.

21:07.382 --> 21:10.874
I'm the Carmines' niece
and when I got here, she had already left.

21:11.320 --> 21:12.878
OWEN:
Just left the children alone?

21:14.156 --> 21:17.125
OWEN: You haven't heard from her since?
- I haven't heard from her.

21:17.292 --> 21:18.589
I didn't even see her.

21:18.894 --> 21:21.624
OWEN: Oh, it's... It's just not...
It's not like her to not call me.

21:24.499 --> 21:27.627
Maybe she just went to a friend's house.
With the storm and all.

21:27.803 --> 21:29.794
OWEN: Yeah, I... I guess so.

21:30.772 --> 21:31.796
I just...

21:31.974 --> 21:33.498
Be sure...

21:33.675 --> 21:36.109
...to tell her that I stopped by
if you see her.

21:36.278 --> 21:37.802
I will.

21:43.418 --> 21:45.283
[THUNDER CRASHING]

21:49.024 --> 21:50.389
[DISHES CLINKING]

22:18.820 --> 22:19.844
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

22:35.904 --> 22:37.235
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

22:49.117 --> 22:50.448
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:14.109 --> 23:16.441
[THUNDER CRASHING]

23:17.079 --> 23:19.070
[LOCKS CLICKING]

23:28.056 --> 23:29.284
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

23:39.768 --> 23:41.099
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

23:51.346 --> 23:53.337
[THUNDER CRACKS]

24:05.527 --> 24:08.985
And what are his special powers?

24:09.231 --> 24:10.459
Um...

24:11.299 --> 24:14.791
Um, he can... He flies.
Swoosh, swoosh.

24:15.604 --> 24:18.732
Oh, yeah, yeah.
And shoots fire from his hands.

24:18.907 --> 24:20.898
[TOY REVS]

24:21.710 --> 24:23.268
[FARTING]

24:23.512 --> 24:24.843
[BOYS GIGGLING]

24:26.014 --> 24:27.208
I tooted.

24:27.382 --> 24:30.044
[ALL GIGGLING]

24:31.653 --> 24:32.950
Excuse me.

24:33.355 --> 24:36.347
[INDISTINCT NOISES OUTSIDE ROOM]

24:38.093 --> 24:40.084
[BOYS MIMIC SHOOTING SOUNDS]

24:48.036 --> 24:49.094
[BOYS CHUCKLE]

24:57.512 --> 24:58.911
[BOYS CHUCKLE]

25:01.183 --> 25:03.743
Okay, men, time to hit the hay.

25:03.919 --> 25:05.011
DANNY:
Aww.

25:07.022 --> 25:09.354
Okay, good night, love bug.

25:09.524 --> 25:11.151
Sleep tight.

25:11.326 --> 25:13.487
- Good night.
MAX: Night, Tabby.

25:17.799 --> 25:20.825
No, no, no, leave it cracked.

25:21.269 --> 25:22.327
TABITHA:
Okay. Shhh.

25:22.504 --> 25:24.267
Just go to sleep.

25:31.646 --> 25:33.637
[SIGHS]

25:38.987 --> 25:40.978
[BANGING]

26:36.011 --> 26:37.103
[CREAKING]

27:11.946 --> 27:13.140
[THUNDER CRASHES]

27:14.349 --> 27:15.475
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

27:28.997 --> 27:30.157
[UNBUCKLES BELT]

27:42.344 --> 27:43.368
[BANGS]

27:43.578 --> 27:44.738
[TV STATIC]

27:55.123 --> 27:56.522
You've gotta be kidding me.

28:02.430 --> 28:03.692
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

28:31.559 --> 28:32.583
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

28:33.228 --> 28:35.128
[THUNDER CRASHING]

28:50.912 --> 28:52.038
[EXHALES]

29:16.571 --> 29:17.799
[SIGHS]

29:40.428 --> 29:44.888
[PHONE RINGING]

29:47.268 --> 29:50.260
[PHONE RINGING]

30:00.615 --> 30:05.814
[PHONE RINGING]

30:09.791 --> 30:12.555
- Hello?
GRACE: <i>Tabitha? It's Aunt Grace.</i>

30:12.727 --> 30:16.356
- <i>Sorry to be calling so late, but you know.</i>
- Yeah, no, no. It's okay.

30:16.531 --> 30:18.294
GRACE:
<i>Oh, I didn't wake you?</i>

30:18.466 --> 30:20.058
No. No.

30:20.735 --> 30:23.795
GRACE: <i>I just wanted to check</i>
<i>on the little ones. How are they?</i>

30:23.972 --> 30:27.430
TABITHA: They're fine. Perfect angels.
They went to bed no problem.

30:27.609 --> 30:28.667
GRACE:
<i>Okay, good.</i>

30:28.843 --> 30:29.867
[TABITHA EXHALES SHARPLY]

30:30.044 --> 30:31.170
TABITHA:
Listen, um...

30:31.846 --> 30:35.077
...I love your new house
but the clown in my room...

30:35.250 --> 30:37.275
No offense, but I hate it.

30:37.452 --> 30:38.851
GRACE:
<i>Oh, God, which one now?</i>

30:40.655 --> 30:41.679
The big one.

30:41.856 --> 30:42.982
GRACE:
<i>Which one?</i>

30:43.157 --> 30:45.148
You know, the really big one.

30:45.326 --> 30:46.793
GRACE:
<i>I'm not sure which one you mean.</i>

30:46.961 --> 30:49.691
TABITHA: The one that sits in the chair.
You know, it's life-size.

30:49.864 --> 30:51.126
The really, really big one.

30:51.299 --> 30:53.665
You have him propped up
in that rocking chair.

30:54.636 --> 30:56.866
GRACE:
<i>Tabby, what...? What are you talking about?</i>

30:57.038 --> 31:00.633
TABITHA: In the guest bedroom,
with all the other clowns.

31:00.808 --> 31:03.038
The one bigger than me.

31:03.211 --> 31:05.042
GRACE:
<i>We... We don't own anything like that.</i>

31:05.213 --> 31:06.840
TABITHA:
Yeah, you do.

31:07.282 --> 31:09.182
I'm looking right at it.

31:13.555 --> 31:14.613
GRACE:
<i>Tabitha.</i>

31:16.391 --> 31:18.086
<i>Tabitha, are you there?</i>

31:18.426 --> 31:20.018
<i>Tabitha!</i>

31:20.194 --> 31:21.991
<i>Tabitha!</i>

31:22.964 --> 31:24.955
[ROCKING]

31:27.702 --> 31:29.693
[DOOR KNOB RATTLING]

31:30.505 --> 31:32.439
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

31:36.578 --> 31:37.977
TABITHA:
Boys.

31:38.346 --> 31:39.370
Wake up.

31:42.483 --> 31:43.882
Boys?

31:44.185 --> 31:46.153
Where are you?

31:46.321 --> 31:47.913
[BANGING]

31:48.189 --> 31:50.180
[TABITHA BREATHING SHARPLY]

31:55.096 --> 31:56.893
What's wrong, Tabby?

31:57.065 --> 31:58.828
Don't be scared.

31:59.000 --> 32:00.661
TABITHA:
Boys, listen to me, we have to hide.

32:00.835 --> 32:03.133
There's a bad man,
a very bad man in the house.

32:03.304 --> 32:05.033
He just wants to play.

32:05.206 --> 32:06.730
Like earlier at the door.

32:07.075 --> 32:08.099
That was him?

32:08.276 --> 32:09.368
[CHUCKLES]

32:09.944 --> 32:11.070
Owen.

32:11.245 --> 32:12.371
TABITHA:
No, don't!

32:12.547 --> 32:15.380
But, Tabby, he said he just wanted
to have some fun.

32:15.550 --> 32:17.541
[SCREAMING]

32:19.887 --> 32:21.149
BOYS:
Help!

32:22.190 --> 32:23.248
Help!

32:25.793 --> 32:27.351
Help!

32:28.696 --> 32:29.720
[CLOWN LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

32:29.897 --> 32:31.762
TABITHA:
Get going.

32:32.033 --> 32:33.398
Come on.

32:37.138 --> 32:38.469
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

32:39.440 --> 32:40.771
[BANGING]

32:45.079 --> 32:46.239
Hurry up, hurry up.

32:46.881 --> 32:48.940
[BANGING]

32:50.218 --> 32:51.412
[WHIMPERS]

33:02.096 --> 33:03.586
[GRUNTING]

33:04.032 --> 33:05.363
[TABITHA BREATHING SHARPLY]

33:08.136 --> 33:10.400
TABITHA:
Boys, run. Get help.

33:11.372 --> 33:13.067
Run.

33:13.808 --> 33:15.139
[CLOWN GROANING]

33:15.476 --> 33:17.467
TABITHA:
Ah... No!

33:17.645 --> 33:18.839
[CLOWN GRUNTING]

33:19.247 --> 33:20.407
TABITHA:
No!

33:21.616 --> 33:23.015
[COUGHING]

33:23.184 --> 33:24.344
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

33:31.859 --> 33:33.224
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

33:35.029 --> 33:36.291
[TABITHA GASPING]

33:38.132 --> 33:39.224
[GRUNTS]

33:41.469 --> 33:42.663
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

33:43.438 --> 33:44.769
[PANTING]

33:48.876 --> 33:50.241
[INHALES SHARPLY]

34:02.090 --> 34:03.421
[CRASHING]

34:05.827 --> 34:07.192
[TABITHA SCREAMING]

34:08.862 --> 34:10.194
[CLOWN LAUGHING MANICALLY]

34:14.135 --> 34:16.569
[SCREAMING]

34:25.947 --> 34:30.475
COP: Miss Wright, do you know anybody
who would want to hurt you?

34:39.327 --> 34:41.726
This whole thing is gonna work out
a lot smoother...

34:41.896 --> 34:44.387
...if you just cooperate with us, okay?

34:44.565 --> 34:48.558
Do you remember anything about the man
who attacked you?

34:53.775 --> 34:55.106
[DOOR BUZZES]

34:58.579 --> 34:59.910
[DOOR CLOSES]

35:00.748 --> 35:02.739
[MANIACAL LAUGHTER]

35:04.886 --> 35:06.877
[CHILDREN CHUCKLING]

35:08.790 --> 35:10.223
CHILD TABITHA [VOICE-OVER]:
<i>Let me see, let me see.</i>

35:10.391 --> 35:12.052
CHILD LAUGH:
<i>Let me look at yours first.</i>

35:12.226 --> 35:14.160
CHILD TABITHA:
<i>Okay, here.</i>

35:16.531 --> 35:18.522
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

35:21.435 --> 35:23.699
CHILD LAUGH:
Tabitha, this is boring.

35:23.871 --> 35:26.533
CHILD TABITHA:
No, it's not. Yours is boring.

35:26.808 --> 35:29.276
CHILD LAUGH:
Mine is better than this.

35:29.443 --> 35:31.104
You'll see.

35:39.453 --> 35:40.613
CHILD TABITHA:
Now let me look in yours.

35:41.189 --> 35:44.283
Not till I see all of yours first.

35:45.960 --> 35:48.451
CHILD LAUGH [VOICE-OVER]:
<i>Um, Shelby.</i>

35:51.332 --> 35:53.527
CHILD LAUGH:
Shelby, yours is worse than Tabitha's.

35:53.701 --> 35:55.931
CHILD SHELBY:
No, it isn't.

35:56.103 --> 35:57.127
CHILD LAUGH:
Lisa.

36:01.175 --> 36:04.474
CHILD LAUGH: Now, what's that?
CHILD LISA: It's a sleepover.

36:05.513 --> 36:07.174
CHILD TABITHA:
Now let us see yours.

36:07.348 --> 36:10.749
CHILD LAUGH:
Okay. One at a time and I have to hold it.

36:12.987 --> 36:15.649
[CHILDREN CHUCKLING]

36:18.392 --> 36:19.723
[CHILD LAUGH CHUCKLES]

36:21.295 --> 36:22.455
It's funny, right?

36:23.064 --> 36:24.759
No.

36:25.700 --> 36:26.962
It isn't.

36:27.134 --> 36:29.102
[CHILD LAUGH CHUCKLING]

36:33.474 --> 36:34.498
CHILD LISA [VOICE-OVER]:
<i>Shelby.</i>

36:36.244 --> 36:38.508
<i>Let's go. Hurry.</i>

36:40.548 --> 36:41.879
[CHILD LAUGH CHUCKLING]

36:43.284 --> 36:44.581
[SHRIEKS]

36:48.222 --> 36:49.519
[MANIACAL LAUGHTER]

36:50.324 --> 36:51.757
[DOOR BUZZES]

37:10.478 --> 37:11.502
Hello, Tabitha.

37:15.650 --> 37:18.380
I'm an on-site trauma counselor
for the state...

37:18.552 --> 37:22.716
...and I'd just like to ask you
a few questions.

37:23.557 --> 37:25.491
All right?

37:34.435 --> 37:38.337
I realize you're in a serious
state of shock...

37:38.806 --> 37:41.775
...so we'll just go at your own pace,
okay?

37:44.578 --> 37:47.240
Do you know a Lisa Swan?

37:49.784 --> 37:51.775
[CHATTERING]

37:59.760 --> 38:01.694
LISA: I'm telling you, dude.
CAT: Stop it.

38:03.064 --> 38:04.998
Don't make me laugh when I'm applying.

38:05.166 --> 38:06.258
You're drunk, Miss Swan.

38:06.434 --> 38:09.631
And you're celibate. Take off
the chastity belt and go home with him.

38:09.804 --> 38:10.930
No.

38:11.105 --> 38:13.300
It's Roommate Night.

38:14.241 --> 38:19.577
Besides, he just moved into town
and he's staying at the Pere's Pension.

38:20.414 --> 38:23.941
- That dump by the park?
- Yeah. But it's temporary.

38:24.118 --> 38:25.915
Be nice.

38:26.087 --> 38:27.884
[CHATTERING]

38:28.856 --> 38:29.880
Mm.

38:31.325 --> 38:33.088
At least let him drive you home.

38:34.028 --> 38:35.552
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

38:36.664 --> 38:38.256
You're right.

38:38.432 --> 38:40.992
- So I'll see you at home in 30, okay?
- Mm-hm.

39:05.059 --> 39:06.390
[LISA EXHALES SHARPLY]

39:07.161 --> 39:09.652
Okay. Okay, stop.

39:10.031 --> 39:12.295
You know I want to
but it's Roommate Night.

39:12.466 --> 39:14.491
And she lives for this shit.

39:14.902 --> 39:16.995
You had to live
with the consummate good girl.

39:17.438 --> 39:20.805
- I know. I'll make it up to you. I promise.
- Yeah.

39:22.476 --> 39:23.875
Bye.

39:25.446 --> 39:26.470
[DOOR CLOSES]

39:37.058 --> 39:38.787
Hey, Cat.

39:41.796 --> 39:44.060
Let's get this night going.

39:57.378 --> 39:58.902
Cat?

40:04.218 --> 40:05.879
Cat?

40:17.765 --> 40:19.756
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

40:21.268 --> 40:22.292
LISA:
Mm.

40:24.572 --> 40:26.836
DAN [ON PHONE]: <i>Hey.</i>
- Hey, baby, it's me.

40:27.007 --> 40:28.167
You can turn back around.

40:28.342 --> 40:30.207
DAN: <i>You're kidding me.</i>
<i>It's Roommate Night.</i>

40:30.377 --> 40:32.811
No, she's not here.
I guess she got lucky.

40:32.980 --> 40:35.608
DAN: <i>Good for Cat.</i>
<i>It had to happen sometime, right?</i>

40:35.783 --> 40:37.580
- I'll see you soon.
DAN: <i>I'll be there.</i>

40:37.751 --> 40:39.048
Bye.

40:39.787 --> 40:41.015
[PHONE CLICKS]

41:05.779 --> 41:06.803
[BED SQUEAKS]

42:01.035 --> 42:03.026
LISA:
It's after 4:00.

42:03.437 --> 42:04.836
She never does this.

42:05.005 --> 42:08.907
She never goes home with a guy
unless she's dated him for a month at least.

42:10.778 --> 42:12.075
Maybe she did.

42:12.246 --> 42:13.508
No.

42:13.681 --> 42:16.275
I mean, we're talking about Cat.
Come on, you know her.

42:17.084 --> 42:19.211
LISA: No, I'm just gonna run over there
real quick.

42:19.386 --> 42:21.286
- Over where?
- The Pere's Pension.

42:21.455 --> 42:23.787
DAN:
Oh, come on, Lise.

42:23.958 --> 42:25.983
You're overreacting.

42:26.160 --> 42:27.286
[DOOR CLOSES]

42:48.282 --> 42:49.613
[GATE CREAKS]

43:12.172 --> 43:14.163
[BELL CLANGS]

43:22.883 --> 43:24.874
[BELL CLANGS]

43:34.762 --> 43:39.199
LISA: Hi, I was wondering if I could...
MAN: Sorry. All the beds are full.

43:39.566 --> 43:40.965
LISA:
But...

43:47.775 --> 43:49.106
[PEEPHOLE CREAKS OPEN]

44:28.682 --> 44:31.207
Now, don't you find it strange
that for a full hotel...

44:31.385 --> 44:34.877
...we haven't seen one person come or go
in over two hours?

44:35.989 --> 44:40.653
Yeah. But, I mean, we're not even sure
that Cat went anywhere near that place.

44:41.128 --> 44:44.120
She's my best friend.
She doesn't do anything without telling me.

44:44.298 --> 44:47.358
And the last person that saw her
is staying there.

44:48.168 --> 44:52.104
I mean, come on, Dan, she hasn't called
all day. That never happens.

44:55.109 --> 44:58.408
Can't you just use your badge?

44:58.846 --> 45:01.644
Lise, I work for the Health Department,
okay? Not the police.

45:01.815 --> 45:02.975
My badge is useless.

45:03.150 --> 45:04.208
Look at that place.

45:04.385 --> 45:07.650
I mean, can't you make something up
just to get in there and see?

45:07.821 --> 45:10.346
Just to see if she's in there.

45:16.530 --> 45:18.157
[BELL CLANGS]

45:33.814 --> 45:34.838
DAN:
Hi there.

45:35.015 --> 45:36.812
MAN:
I'm sorry, I can't help you.

45:37.217 --> 45:38.878
All of our beds are full tonight.

45:39.052 --> 45:42.283
DAN: That's all right, sir. I'm actually...
I'm from the Health Department.

45:42.489 --> 45:43.922
Just need a moment.

45:49.530 --> 45:51.521
[KEYS RATTLING]

46:11.351 --> 46:12.375
[EXHALES]

46:14.188 --> 46:15.519
[DOOR LOCKING]

46:25.933 --> 46:26.957
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

47:04.271 --> 47:06.637
MAN:
How may I help you?

47:08.375 --> 47:10.240
Well, the neighbors were complaining.

47:10.844 --> 47:12.835
Uh, seems they're getting
some vermin from here.

47:13.013 --> 47:16.141
We just wanted to let you know
before a formal complaint was made.

47:16.316 --> 47:18.443
- The neighbors, huh?
- Yeah.

47:18.919 --> 47:20.352
That's interesting.

47:22.189 --> 47:23.213
Hm.

47:23.423 --> 47:25.584
Like I said, it's nothing serious as of yet.

47:26.426 --> 47:28.291
Sir, will you pardon me for a moment?

47:29.296 --> 47:30.695
- Yeah.
- You can go ahead...

47:30.864 --> 47:32.491
...and wait in the gaming room.

47:35.669 --> 47:37.000
[DAN EXHALES SHARPLY]

48:45.472 --> 48:48.771
MAN:
It's a metal scope Victrola.

48:50.811 --> 48:51.835
Oh.

48:54.147 --> 48:56.274
It's very old.

48:56.950 --> 48:58.577
And priceless.

49:00.120 --> 49:01.519
What's it do?

49:01.688 --> 49:03.679
What does it do?

49:06.059 --> 49:07.890
Well, it plays a song.

49:08.061 --> 49:10.427
And at the end, you get a surprise.

49:10.597 --> 49:11.928
[DAN EXHALES SHARPLY]

49:12.566 --> 49:13.965
Well, go on. Try it.

49:14.134 --> 49:16.068
Oh, no, no. That's okay.

49:16.236 --> 49:17.703
Try it.

49:19.740 --> 49:21.401
Okay.

49:29.349 --> 49:31.340
[CREEPY MUSIC PLAYING]

49:38.458 --> 49:40.323
Where did you find this thing?

49:40.494 --> 49:42.553
Well, I come from a long line...

49:43.664 --> 49:46.497
...of entertainers and performers.

49:46.867 --> 49:48.994
You know, lovers of the laugh.

50:01.882 --> 50:03.213
[GRUNTS]

50:03.417 --> 50:04.475
[CRASHING]

50:04.818 --> 50:06.149
[MAN LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

50:12.325 --> 50:13.656
[OWL HOOTING]

50:17.564 --> 50:19.555
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

50:23.370 --> 50:25.361
[CELL PHONE DIALING]

50:27.841 --> 50:29.934
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

50:33.213 --> 50:35.704
DAN [ON VOICEMAIL RECORDING]:
<i>Hey, this is Dan. Leave me a message.</i>

50:35.882 --> 50:36.906
[VOICEMAIL BEEPS]

50:37.150 --> 50:39.641
Dan, why aren't you answering?

50:39.820 --> 50:40.946
It's me again.

50:43.090 --> 50:46.355
Please call me back.
I'm panicking here, okay?

50:47.494 --> 50:49.462
Where are you?

50:51.565 --> 50:53.055
[CELL PHONE CLICKS SHUT]

51:28.869 --> 51:29.893
[BOTTLE CLATTERS]

51:30.537 --> 51:31.868
[LISA BREATHES SHARPLY]

51:37.911 --> 51:39.242
[DOOR OPENS]

51:40.213 --> 51:41.544
[LISA INHALES SHARPLY]

52:37.204 --> 52:38.694
[BROKEN GLASS CLATTERS]

52:39.339 --> 52:40.670
[BROKEN GLASS CRUNCHES]

52:43.476 --> 52:44.807
[INHALES SHARPLY]

52:50.917 --> 52:52.885
[PANTING]

53:05.265 --> 53:06.926
[PANTING]

54:13.066 --> 54:15.034
LISA:
Excuse me.

54:15.435 --> 54:17.494
Can you help me?

54:18.071 --> 54:20.062
[LISA BREATHES SHARPLY]

54:21.741 --> 54:22.935
Please...

54:23.877 --> 54:24.901
Um...

54:25.078 --> 54:26.102
[MAN MUTTERING]

54:26.313 --> 54:29.714
I... I... I need to find someone.
He came in here a while ago.

54:30.150 --> 54:31.481
[WHIMPERING]

54:33.386 --> 54:34.944
Please, uh...

54:35.655 --> 54:38.385
Oh, um...

54:38.591 --> 54:39.785
[GIBBERING]

54:41.127 --> 54:44.619
Um, I need to find someone in here.

54:46.633 --> 54:48.225
GUEST:
I'm sorry.

54:48.568 --> 54:51.560
I need read lips.

54:55.008 --> 54:57.670
Okay, good. Good.

54:58.244 --> 54:59.370
Um...

55:00.380 --> 55:01.745
I need...

55:01.915 --> 55:02.939
...to find someone.

55:04.951 --> 55:07.146
- Okay.
- Okay.

55:07.320 --> 55:10.153
Um, a man. My friend...

55:10.523 --> 55:13.117
...uh, came here hours ago.

55:13.593 --> 55:15.060
Did you see anyone?

55:16.997 --> 55:19.989
No one come in here.

55:20.767 --> 55:21.859
[SIGHS]

55:23.003 --> 55:24.527
Okay. Um...

55:24.971 --> 55:25.995
[SIGHS]

55:26.172 --> 55:27.799
Another friend...

55:27.974 --> 55:30.101
...a girl, came here last night.

55:30.577 --> 55:32.272
Did you see a girl?

55:32.712 --> 55:34.111
I mean, where is everyone?

55:34.714 --> 55:36.705
[GIBBERING]

55:36.916 --> 55:38.907
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

55:40.987 --> 55:46.118
Um, okay, there's a man, an angry man.

55:46.593 --> 55:50.051
He don't let us leave.

55:51.965 --> 55:53.193
LISA:
Um...

55:56.436 --> 55:57.994
[LISA BREATHING HEAVILY]

55:58.304 --> 56:00.135
GUEST:
No. No, no.

56:00.306 --> 56:02.103
You hide. You hide.

56:02.275 --> 56:04.903
- What?
- Hide in here.

56:05.612 --> 56:07.204
- Where do I...? Hide?
- He come very soon.

56:07.380 --> 56:10.816
- You mean hide?
- Hide. He come very soon.

56:13.186 --> 56:15.848
He come very soon.

56:17.757 --> 56:19.088
[GUEST WHIMPERING]

56:24.864 --> 56:26.195
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

56:28.435 --> 56:29.766
[PHONE BEEPS]

56:30.703 --> 56:32.694
[LISA BREATHES SHARPLY]

56:36.676 --> 56:37.904
[SCREAMING]

56:49.122 --> 56:50.453
[MUFFLED WHIMPERING]

56:51.491 --> 56:53.186
CAT [MUFFLED]:
Lisa.

56:53.359 --> 56:56.726
[CAT SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

56:56.896 --> 56:58.887
[CRYING]

57:05.038 --> 57:06.198
[LISA SCREAMS]

57:09.075 --> 57:10.406
[WHIMPERING]

57:12.645 --> 57:15.239
Please help me.
Please, my friend. My friend.

57:15.415 --> 57:16.848
She's alive in here.

57:17.016 --> 57:18.040
CAT [MUFFLED]:
No. No.

57:18.885 --> 57:20.045
CAT: No!
LISA: Cat!

57:20.487 --> 57:22.079
LISA: Oh, God, Cat.
CAT: No, no...

57:22.255 --> 57:24.780
LISA: Cat, it'll be okay!
CAT: He's not...

57:24.958 --> 57:28.223
LISA: Please, help me get her out. Please.
CAT: He's not...

57:28.595 --> 57:30.586
[CAT CRYING]

57:33.933 --> 57:36.094
[MUFFLED]
He's not... He's...

57:36.803 --> 57:38.566
He's...

57:38.738 --> 57:40.763
[GUEST HUMMING GIBBERISH]

57:42.675 --> 57:45.576
[CAT SCREAMING AND CRYING MUFFLED]

57:53.920 --> 57:55.410
CAT [MUFFLED AND CRYING]:
He's...

58:00.360 --> 58:01.827
[CHUCKLES]

58:02.028 --> 58:05.020
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

58:09.502 --> 58:12.369
[SCREAMING]

58:13.039 --> 58:15.030
[LAUGHING MANIACALLY]

58:26.319 --> 58:29.447
PSYCHIATRIST:
So you did know Lisa Swan.

58:29.822 --> 58:32.620
But you don't know Rob Ellerbe?

58:34.427 --> 58:36.657
Maybe you know his girlfriend...

58:36.829 --> 58:38.194
...Shelby Leds.

58:39.899 --> 58:41.696
Shelby?

58:42.302 --> 58:44.202
What's Shelby got to do with this?

58:44.871 --> 58:46.600
You tell me.

58:50.343 --> 58:55.713
Shelby and Lisa and I,
we were inseparable.

58:55.882 --> 58:57.975
But I haven't seen them in years.

58:58.151 --> 59:00.312
Not since we were kids in Briar Hills.

59:01.688 --> 59:04.851
Briar Hills.

59:05.358 --> 59:07.849
That's a subdivision of Columbus,
isn't it?

59:10.763 --> 59:11.787
How did you know?

59:12.398 --> 59:13.422
Um...

59:13.833 --> 59:15.164
[CELL PHONE CLICKS OPEN]

59:16.169 --> 59:17.193
[SIGHS]

59:17.370 --> 59:18.394
[CELL PHONE CLICKS SHUT]

59:18.571 --> 59:20.801
Miss, you need to stay here.

59:20.974 --> 59:23.306
How did you know about Briar Hills?

59:26.246 --> 59:28.009
I had a patient.

59:28.181 --> 59:29.773
A boy.

59:29.949 --> 59:31.644
Years ago.

59:32.452 --> 59:35.250
One of my first asylum cases.

59:35.888 --> 59:38.015
He was from Briar Hills.

59:41.194 --> 59:43.685
I've never met anyone who...

59:46.599 --> 59:49.796
He had the most distinctive laugh.

59:50.069 --> 59:52.003
TABITHA:
Where...? Where are you going?

59:52.171 --> 59:54.469
I just need to find a phone that works.

59:54.641 --> 59:56.609
Don't worry, I'll be back for you
and your friends.

59:56.776 --> 59:57.800
[DOOR BUZZES]

59:57.977 --> 59:59.137
They're here?

59:59.312 --> 01:00:00.939
Shelby and Lisa?

01:00:01.114 --> 01:00:02.809
Yeah.

01:00:03.783 --> 01:00:08.015
The three of you were found
in separate cells in this building.

01:00:08.187 --> 01:00:10.178
[PSYCHIATRIST INHALES SHARPLY]

01:00:10.423 --> 01:00:13.392
A call went out for a trauma couns...

01:00:17.597 --> 01:00:19.292
Oh, God!

01:00:19.465 --> 01:00:21.558
No, no, don't leave me here.

01:00:21.734 --> 01:00:23.634
Don't leave me here!

01:00:23.803 --> 01:00:25.100
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:01:00.640 --> 01:01:01.902
[DOOR BUZZES]

01:01:02.108 --> 01:01:03.336
[DOOR SQUEAKS OPEN]

01:01:34.707 --> 01:01:35.867
[DOOR CREAKS]

01:01:50.390 --> 01:01:52.051
Shelby?

01:01:55.061 --> 01:01:56.790
Lisa?

01:02:06.139 --> 01:02:07.800
[WATER DRIPPING]

01:02:35.601 --> 01:02:36.795
[LIGHT BUZZES]

01:02:41.474 --> 01:02:42.805
[FOOTSTEPS]

